    <briefdescription>
<para>This class uses <ref refid="classwx_html_help_controller" kindref="compound">wxHtmlHelpController</ref> to display help in a modal dialog. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is useful on platforms such as wxMac where if you display help from a modal dialog, the help window must itself be a modal dialog.</para><para>Create objects of this class on the stack, for example:</para><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">//<sp/>The<sp/>help<sp/>can<sp/>be<sp/>browsed<sp/>during<sp/>the<sp/>lifetime<sp/>of<sp/>this<sp/>object;<sp/>when<sp/>the</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">//<sp/>user<sp/>quits<sp/>the<sp/>help,<sp/>program<sp/>execution<sp/>will<sp/>continue.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">wxHtmlModalHelp<sp/>help(parent,<sp/>&quot;help&quot;,<sp/>&quot;My<sp/>topic&quot;);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para><para><heading level="2"></heading>
